                <div class="col-sm-6">
                    <h1 class="galleryHeader">About the band</h1>
                    <p>Mac Fontana and Big D formed the duo in 2015, after years of playing in bands. “We wanted to make things 
                    simple—sing together and play songs for people without the onslaught of a blasting band,” says Big D. 
                    The combination of D on acoustic guitar and Mac on keys allows them to draw on a range of sounds adaptable 
                    to anything from Beatles classics to Elton John’s “Tiny Dancer” to something as quirky as Bowie’s “Space Oddity.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                    Actually, calling Mac Fontana and Big D a duo may be misleading—for many of their shows they enlist drummer Mark E to keep things moving.
                    Guitar and piano alone perfectly suit a quiet song such as the Beatles’ “Hide Your Love Away.” Mac says, “Then, when Mark kicks the drums 
                    in and I cover the bass, suddenly it’s a whole band on songs like Counting Crows’ ‘Mr. Jones and Me’ or Queen’s 
                    ‘Crazy Little Thing Called Love.’” 
                    </p>
                    <p>
                    Starting in the fall of 2015, the group has been entertaining audiences at Fiesta Hermosa, Pickwick’s Pub, the Oyster House Saloon, and a number of private events. So enjoy the music and the harmonies—and let the dancing begin. 
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="col-sm-6">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
